
To load the table.el library type in load-library *table* or use the two
functions *table-insert* or *table-recognize*.

** Commands

- *table-recognize*     [H-z H-t t] recognizes tables in buffer
- *table-insert*        [H-z H-t i] inserts a new table at point
- *table-insert-row*    [H-z H-t r] inserts a new row before point
- *table-insert-column* [H-z H-t c] inserts a new column before point
- *table-justify*       [H-z H-t j] justifies a row, column or cell


** Standard Commands

 - *C-+* - insert row/column
 - *C-<* - narrow cell
 - *C->* - widen cell
 - *C-^* - generates from source another language
